data.text:
It’s Canada Day, the day that much of the northern part of the North American continent became master of its own destiny, sort of. Over time, more and more provinces were added until the country had borders on three oceans. From these 10 provinces and 3 territories come all sorts of artists, performers, inventors, writers, musicians, actors and activists, snacks, books, movies, and more, of all sorts.

Celebrate your favourites here!
